node.text: Working on some new music for 2020 over the holiday period (for me + others!) - can’t wait to get it out this coming year!! 📸: @meabh_fitzpatrick_photography

Christmas concert for the residents of the Sacred Heart hospital in my hometown of Carlow with my 💜
This hospital is a special place for both of our families, music is our way of saying thanks to the staff there and spreading a little bit of holiday cheer among the residents 🎄

Delighted to be an Official Showcase Artist at Folk Alliance this year! Can’t wait to showcase on Thursday 23rd January 2020 at 4:30pm in the Maurepas Room! Thanks to @cultureireland and the @folk_alliance for their help in getting there.

Great to see my friend Udo Rösner last night at the show in Bochum. He brought along his new Udo Roesner Amps “Da Capo” for me to use - what a sound. I’m really excited to work on some more projects with him in search of “the sound”! Thanks to all who came out yesterday evening and yesterday night. Tonight is my final show of the year: Oldenburg at Wilhelm13. Doors 7pm, Show 8pm. Can’t wait! #shanehennessy #udoroesner #udorösner #acousticamp #livemusic #guitarsound #acousticsound #udoamps #dacapoamp #germantour #germany #deutschland

I am ready for this weekend's shows in Germany! Thanks to Udo Roesner Amps for my brand new Da Capo 75 amp - it's the best amp I've ever used. Thanks also to Maton Guitars for sending me a brand new Maton AP5Pro pickup. My sound has never been this good! Hoping to see some of my German fans this weekend. Tickets and info via https://www.shanehennessy.ie/shows

It was nice to jump up with friends @themoxiestrings at their show in Dublin last night! Doing one more “jump up” this week tomorrow evening in Kilkenny at the Set Theatre with good friends @scythianmusic ! #shanehennessy #moxiestrings #cobblestone #dublin

My new album is written, demos are being made, and I’m planning to record it all at the end of November, for release in early 2020. Cannot wait to get this out and into your ears!! It has also been great getting my Maton Traditional back into my hands after drying it out - it’s sounding better than ever! The newer 808TEc is staying with me as its formidable companion. More about the new album very soon...

📸: Scott Murrish < @scott_murrish_photography >
